@TITLE "snapconv(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name snapconv - Sinclair ZX Spectrum snapshot convertor @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}snapconv@{"ub"} [ -c ] [ -n ] @{"i"}infile@{"ui"} outfile @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description Snapconv converts between ZX Spectrum snapshot files. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Options @{"i"}-c@{"ui"} specifies that all data in the output snapshot should be compressed, even if that compression will result in a bigger file than if some data is left uncompressed. This helps compatibility with some buggy programs that can only read entirely compressed .z80 files. @{"i"}-n@{"ui"} specifies that the output snapshot should be uncompressed. @{"i"}infile@{"ui"} specifies the snapshot to be converted. This file can be in any of the snapshot formats supported by @{" " link "'libspectrum.3'/MAIN"}@{"i"}libspectrum@{"ui"}(3) . @{"i"}outfile@{"ui"} specifies the output snapshot. The format will be determined by the file extension and can be in any of the formats @{" " link "'libspectrum.3'/MAIN"}@{"i"}libspectrum@{"ui"}(3) supports for output. @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}Bugs None known. @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'fuse.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'fuse-utils.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse-utils@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'libspectrum.3'/MAIN"}@{"i"}libspectrum@{"ui"}(3) , @{" " link "'listbasic.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}listbasic@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'snap2tzx.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}snap2tzx@{"ui"}(1) 

The comp.sys.sinclair Spectrum FAQ, at 
@{" " link "'http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html.guide/MAIN"}@{"i"}http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html@{"ui"}. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Author Philip Kendall (philip-fuse@shadowmagic.org.uk). 


